    Designing for Responsible Interaction: This view necessitates designing AI systems that are constantly aware of their representational nature and their reliance on human-provided data and context. It highlights the critical need for transparency, interpretability, and robust alignment mechanisms to ensure that the "solutions" AI offers (which might be incredibly powerful in the abstract) are truly beneficial and meaningfully grounded in human reality and values.\par
